y:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-430_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-431_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-432_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-433_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The NMC sets standards of education, training, conduct, and performance so that nurses and midwives can deliver high-quality healthcare throughout their careers. The NMC ensures that nurses and midwives keep their skills and knowledge up to date and uphold our professional standards.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-435_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-436_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="71e56452-a6b7-473d-b1cc-4d83830a32e4" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>Can I revalidate if I'm not currently practising?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="71e56452-a6b7-473d-b1cc-4d83830a32e4" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-438_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-439_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-440_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-441_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Even if you're not currently practising, you can still revalidate with the NMC. The process entails demonstrating that you've met practice and professional development standards over the past three years. This includes maintaining practice hours, engaging in CPD, and providing reflective accounts. Meeting these requirements is essential for successful revalidation and maintaining your NMC registration.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-443_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-444_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="773db1cc-4d83-430a-b2e4-110226d22d38" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>How often do I need to revalidate with NMC?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="773db1cc-4d83-430a-b2e4-110226d22d38" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-446_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-447_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-448_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-449_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">NMC revalidation occurs every three years, coinciding with your registration renewal date.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-451_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-452_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="4105ac0a-ff37-4b35-8b6f-661a05715b87" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>How long does UK NMC verification take?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="4105ac0a-ff37-4b35-8b6f-661a05715b87" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-454_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-455_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-456_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-457_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">NMC aims to process the application within 60 days once they have received all required documents. When everything is completed, you will be invited to take the OSCE exam in your assigned UK hospital.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-459_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-460_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="331136a0-bf35-4eb7-91d4-c55e27eb463d" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>What happens if I don’t meet the revalidation requirements?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="331136a0-bf35-4eb7-91d4-c55e27eb463d" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-462_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-463_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-464_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-465_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Loss of registration</strong> - Your registration with the NMC will lapse, meaning you will no longer be legally allowed to practice as a nurse or midwife in the UK.<br><br><strong>Inability to work</strong> - Without NMC registration, you won't be able to work professionally, which could impact your employment status and income.<br><br><strong>Re-application process</strong> - You may need to go through the re-application process to regain your registration, which can be time-consuming and may involve additional requirements.<br><br><strong>Professional implications</strong> - Failing to revalidate on time can affect your professional reputation and relationships with employers and colleagues.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-467_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-468_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="9597d5c4-1d20-4b83-8e32-0ab0fff81e38" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>Why is it important to revalidate?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="9597d5c4-1d20-4b83-8e32-0ab0fff81e38" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-470_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-471_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-472_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-473_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Revalidation gives patients, the public, employers, and other healthcare professionals greater assurance that licensed doctors are current in their practice and fit to work.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-475_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-476_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="8f9942ca-b68e-477f-8e52-8d2fb4c4e574" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>Why is reflection important in nursing NMC?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="8f9942ca-b68e-477f-8e52-8d2fb4c4e574" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-478_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-479_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-480_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-481_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Reflection on practice is crucial for both students and registered professionals, serving as a key component of NMC revalidation. It aims to nurture self-awareness and understanding, fostering continuous improvement in practice.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-483_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-484_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="d4ad0b32-7b2d-41a7-87c3-abf662bb7e8e" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>Why is it important to adhere to the NMC code?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="d4ad0b32-7b2d-41a7-87c3-abf662bb7e8e" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-486_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-487_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-488_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-489_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The Code contains a series of statements that taken together signify what good practice by nurses, midwives and nursing associates looks like. It puts the interests of patients and service users first, is safe and effective, and promotes trust through professionalism.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-491_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-492_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="4963ec9f-1e46-40e4-b687-7a9e94670d84" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>What is the difference between revalidation and re-registration?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="4963ec9f-1e46-40e4-b687-7a9e94670d84" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-494_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-495_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-496_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-497_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Each year a nurse is required to submit an annual payment to NMC to maintain
registration status. Revalidation occurs every 3 years and requires all nurses to
submit evidence to remain on the register. 
</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-499_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-500_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="6fc61dbe-1165-4f97-9353-50f5661aeff1" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>Can I use my Mandatory Training as evidence of CPD?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="6fc61dbe-1165-4f97-9353-50f5661aeff1" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-502_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-503_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-504_"><p class="sc-fPrdjK gxzXqc pf-505_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">You can only use mandatory training if it is directly related to your scope of practice
as a nurse or midwife. For example, fire or health and safety training should not be
Included. Only mandatory training that is necessary to your scope of practice and professional development as a nurse (for example, CPR or safeguarding training) should be included.
</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-7c06" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-epRwmx cpmRjY pf-507_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-djVWQC dKziBg"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-508_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-509_"></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-510_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-511_"><div data-pf-type="Custom.HTML" class="sc-boZfnm jvQCDP pf-512_"><div class="powr-form-builder" id="3019efda_1752673058"></div>
